helpdesk-ticket.subject: Fwd: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I changed my password last week. Does the notification not reset?
Doug Nelson
Sent from my iPad
Begin forwarded message:
From: <fimservice@msoe.edu<mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu>> Date: December 21, 2015 at 1:00:19 AM CST To: <nelsondj@msoe.edu<mailto:nelsondj@msoe.edu>> Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Your MSOE account password is scheduled to expire on 12/27/2015. [MSOE Logo] [Milwaukee School of Engineering] <http://www.msoe.edu> Hello Douglas,
The password for your MSOE account (nelsondj@msoe.edu<mailto:nelsondj@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 12/27/2015. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 12/27/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters * Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items: * Uppercase letter * Lowercase letter * A number * A symbol
Note: The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu> if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.?
Thank you, The MSOE Help Desk (414) 277-7288
This email was sent by an automated process.
Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 North Broadway * Milwaukee, WI 53202-3109 (800) 332-6763 / explore@msoe.edu<mailto:explore@msoe.edu>

On Mon, 4 Jan at 9:22 pm , Rob <hasker@msoe.edu> wrote:
I’m on overload this term and too snowed under during the day to stand at the help desk for an hour. I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I suspect something has to change in the procedure for Windows 10. I go to File, Add account and get to the Auto Account Setup page. I enter hasker@msoe.edu for the email address, the correct password, and click on Next. It appears to configure correctly getting through to the “log in to server” step. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook. When I exit Outlook from the File menu and restart it, it says “Loading Profile” for a while (5-10 minutes) and then pops up a message saying “The connection to Microsoft Exchange is unavailable. Outlook must be online or connected to complete this action.” It sounds like the left hand isn’t talking to the right, hence my question about whether there’s a tested procedure for reading email in Outlook 2010 on Windows 10.

Thanks.

Rob

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Merged from ticket 4199

Subject: Re: Message from Peter Pfister (7202)

Description:
I’m on overload this term and too snowed under during the day to stand at the help desk for an hour. I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I suspect something has to change in the procedure for Windows 10. I go to File, Add account and get to the Auto Account Setup page. I enter hasker@msoe.edu for the email address, the correct password, and click on Next. It appears to configure correctly getting through to the “log in to server” step. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook. When I exit Outlook from the File menu and restart it, it says “Loading Profile” for a while (5-10 minutes) and then pops up a message saying “The connection to Microsoft Exchange is unavailable. Outlook must be online or connected to complete this action.” It sounds like the left hand isn’t talking to the right, hence my question about whether there’s a tested procedure for reading email in Outlook 2010 on Windows 10.

Thanks.

Rob

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Account Disable Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello! I've received several emails warning me that my account will be disabled as of January 20th. I am a current graduate student who will be registering for classes again for the spring 2016 quarter. How can I continue to keep my accounts active during this time? thank you, Shawn Verdoni
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello!
I've received several emails warning me that my account will be disabled as of January 20th.  I am a current graduate student who will be registering for classes again for the spring 2016 quarter.  How can I continue to keep my accounts active during this time?

thank you,
Shawn Verdoni

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Verdonism,
Our database currently uses an automated system that manages accounts that should or shouldn't be disabled. With our current setup, it is not possible to make exceptions for the accounts that going to be disabled unless the student registers for classes.
Since you are a graduate student, you should be able to create an Alumni account at https://gapps.msoe.edu/
This account will not carry over information from your msoe.edu account but this account will not be disabled whenever you are not registered for classes.
If you have any further questions please do not hesitate to contact us. Thank you for your time, and we apologize for the inconvenience.
Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/4044 Hello! I've received several emails warning me that my account will be disabled as of January 20th. I am a current graduate student who will be registering for classes again for the spring 2016 quarter. How can I continue to keep my accounts active during this time?
thank you, Shawn Verdoni
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Verdonism,

Our database currently uses an automated system that manages accounts that should or shouldn't be disabled. With our current setup, it is not possible to make exceptions for the accounts that going to be disabled unless the student registers for classes.

Since you are a graduate student, you should be able to create an Alumni account at https://gapps.msoe.edu/

This account will not carry over information from your msoe.edu account but this account will not be disabled whenever you are not registered for classes.

If you have any further questions please do not hesitate to contact us. Thank you for your time, and we apologize for the inconvenience.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Andrew Rux,
All MSOE account passwords expire every 90 days as per the security policy. This does not mean that your account will be deactivated. It's just a protocall that forces people to change there passwords on a regular basis. This is standard procedure for students, faculty and staff. If you would like help changing your password, feel free to contact us and we can provide instructions. We can also reset your password remotely to the MSOE default password should it expire before you are able to change it. Thank you and have a nice day. helpdesk-ticket.subject: printer issues in CC202
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I am having difficulties printing to the two printers in the CBM. Peter Pfister came down today to start troubleshooting - but I wanted to document the current issues before I forget.
"CC-202 CBM Xerox 6506 on printers" is on the printers server. It was giving an error message about a document in the queue. NOTE THAT THIS ISSUE HAS SELF RESOLVED following two other events (see below).
The HP Color LaserJet M553 PCL6 printer has been installed 3 times on my printer (we had issues in the past with slow printing because it was working off the wrong server). I CAN print from the installation labeled "CBM Main HP", but we have been unsuccessful in uninstalling the two other versions ("CBM Main" and "HP Color LaserJet M553 PCL6").
We tried: Rebooting my computer Rebooting the printer
Peter said he'd have to do some more investigating.
THEN....I tried printing something, and there were NO printers installed. After rebooting, all printers were restored AND I can now print to both the Xerox and HP printers.
BUT - I still can't remove printers that I don't want from my list.
Hope this information helps with the troubleshooting!
Margaret
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I am having difficulties printing to the two printers in the CBM. Peter Pfister came down today to start troubleshooting – but I wanted to document the current issues before I forget.
 
“CC-202 CBM Xerox 6506 on printers” is on the printers server. It was giving an error message about a document in the queue. NOTE THAT THIS ISSUE HAS SELF RESOLVED following two other events (see below).
 
The HP Color LaserJet M553 PCL6 printer has been installed 3 times on my printer (we had issues in the past with slow printing because it was working off the wrong server). I CAN print from the installation labeled “CBM Main HP”, but we have been unsuccessful in uninstalling the two other versions (“CBM Main” and “HP Color LaserJet M553 PCL6”).
 
We tried:
Rebooting my computer
Rebooting the printer
 
Peter said he’d have to do some more investigating.
 
THEN….I tried printing something, and there were NO printers installed.

BUT – I still can’t remove printers that I don’t want from my list.
 
Hope this information helps with the troubleshooting!
 
Margaret

If the two unused printers wouldn't uninstalled from the laptop correctly run the following command from an admin cmd
printui.exe /dn /n "network path of printer" printui.exe /dl /n "printer name" if you have issues with that run net stop spooler and run it again.

helpdesk-note.body:
Currently, the Grohmann Tower network resides on the academic circuit. It is the only residence that does, due to a delay in fiber by the City. Until we have City fiber, this traffic is running daily at volumes several times higher than the top 10 nearest users combined. This puts a strain on the academic circuit, and the much smaller bandwidth available to the entire Grohmann Tower.
At this point, until city fiber is run, or the traffic can be substantially reduced, this blacklist will remain in place.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi parksh,
How often are you running these backups, and is there any way you can reduce the amount of traffic that you are sending over a greater period of time? This traffic is getting flagged as suspicious, and due to the high volume of bytes in a short period of time over a limited resource of bandwidth that is intended to supply all the residence of the Tower, it's getting blocked. At this time, we cannot guarantee that high volumes of traffic to this site will not be flagged and blacklisted as suspicious. Whatever you can do to reduce the high usage of bandwidth may address the issue. Please remember, the internet circuit that this traffic is saturating is expected to provide internet access for the entire Tower residence. Traffic that uses undue amounts of shared bandwidth is subject to blacklisting.

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello Help Desk.
Happy New Year!
I have an incoming GRADUATE student who wonders if we (MSOE) have any form of a Laptop Purchase or Rental Program for MSOE students. I understand that MSOE Undergrads get laptops as part of their tuition and that benefit is NOT extended to Graduate Students. HOWEVER, it seems like a good question -- is there an MSOE discount on purchase or rental of Laptops BEYOND those offered by Manufacturers such as Apple, Microsoft or Dell? ( I know they offer "educational discounts" of around 10% direct to students or educators WITH a School ID)
Thank you.
Gene

Hello IT, I am teaching Control Systems (EE 3720) this winter quarter. For the labs, we are in room S-344. I believe that the other 3720 instructors have had this same issue as me. Here are the computers that have (at least) log-in issues (Note: Room description [left-to-right or from door to opposite wall - assuming person is looking at board from back of room]): * 1st (Front) Row: 2 connected benches with 2 computers (2nd computer on right) and 2 connected benches with 2 computers (2nd computer on right). * 2nd (Middle) Row: 1 unconnected bench with 1 computer (only computer), space in room with compass, and then 1 unconnected bench with 1 computer. 3rd (Last) Row: 1 unconnected bench with 1 computer, 2 connected benches with 2 computers, and 1 unconnected bench with 1 computer.) (No issues.)
Could you please fix these log-in issues to allow students to log onto the computers and access Matlab to run their labs? Thank you again, Marek
Dr. Marek Trawicki Adjunct Assistant Professor Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Allen-Bradley Hall of Science, S205B 432 E. Kilbourn Avenue, Milwaukee, WI 53202 trawicki@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I have been using Office online for email. I just tried to check email with regular Outlook and it is unable to connect. At one time it it was working so I suspect it is because I changed my login password? Can you let me know how to update my password in Outlook?
Thanks, Mark
Mark Daugherty
Mechanical Engineering
Milwaukee School of Engineering
414-277-2266
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,

I have been using Office online for email.  I just tried to check email with regular Outlook and it is unable to connect.  At one time it it was working so I suspect it is because I changed my login password?  Can you let me know how to update my password in Outlook?

Thanks,
Mark


Mark Daugherty
Mechanical Engineering
Milwaukee School of Engineering
414-277-2266

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark Daugherty,
We can guide you through this, first start off at the windows icon and enter 'CREDENTIAL MANAGER' and then under GENERIC CREDENTIALS , click 'modify' under which you can find 'remove from vault'. Shut outlook and restart again, entering the new password and you're good. If you have any more questions please reach us back.
Shravanthi Bangalore IT Helpdesk Technician
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mark Daugherty,

We can guide you through this, first start off at the windows icon and enter 'CREDENTIAL MANAGER' and then under GENERIC CREDENTIALS , click 'modify' under which you can find 'remove from vault'. Shut outlook and restart again, entering the new password and you're good.
If you have any more questions please reach us back.

Shravanthi Bangalore
IT Helpdesk Technician

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Shravanthi,
It worked great!
Thank you, Mark

helpdesk-ticket.subject: L304 projector would not turn on.
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I arrived this PM to teach my 2710 class in L304. The projection system was turned off and the projectors were both off. I pressed the start system button on the Crestron to start up the system. The Crestron was on and receiving video from both my laptop and the desktop PC (green dot versus red dot.) I tried to send the video from HDMI to both projectors. However, the projectors had not turned on. I climbed up on a chair and manually started both projectors, and while the projectors turned on, they displayed a message NO HDMI signal on the whiteboard. I tried switching to and from various inputs on the Crestron. No changes occurred. I then shutdown the system at the Crestron and waited as class was starting for 2 minute shutdown cycle. The syst5em was brought back online, but no changes were noted. I could not get video from the Crestron to the projectors.
As I shutdown the system now, I can see that the Crestron is shutting down, but the projectors are not responding.
This is a major issue, as I was unable to project any of my materials in class today, and this is a computer programming course.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Re: Message from Peter Pfister (7202)
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I’m on overload this term and too snowed under during the day to stand at the help desk for an hour. I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I suspect something has to change in the procedure for Windows 10. I go to File, Add account and get to the Auto Account Setup page. I enter hasker@msoe.edu for the email address, the correct password, and click on Next. It appears to configure correctly getting through to the “log in to server” step. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook. When I exit Outlook from the File menu and restart it, it says “Loading Profile” for a while (5-10 minutes) and then pops up a message saying “The connection to Microsoft Exchange is unavailable. Outlook must be online or connected to complete this action.” It sounds like the left hand isn’t talking to the right, hence my question about whether there’s a tested procedure for reading email in Outlook 2010 on Windows 10.
Thanks.
Rob
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I’m on overload this term and too snowed under during the day to stand at the help desk for an hour. I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook.
